[4] China (Macau) ex Thailand
Date: Fri 3 Aug 2018
Source: Macau News [edited]
https://macaunews.mo/health-bureau-records-2nd-imported-case-of-measles/


The Health Bureau (SSM) said in a statement Thursday, 2 Aug 2018, that it has recorded the 2nd imported case of measles this year. According to the statement, the patient is a 41 year old local man who visited Phuket with his family on 18-24 Jul [2018]. After returning to Macau, he came down with a fever on 25 Jul 2018 and a rash all over his body last Saturday, 28 Jul 2018. He went to the Island Emergency Station of the public Conde de S. Janu√°rio Hospital Centre in Taipa for treatment the next afternoon [29 Jul 2018].

He consulted a doctor at the private Kiang Wu Hospital where he was hospitalized in the morning on Monday [30 Jul 2018]. He was confirmed to have measles by the bureau's public health laboratory yesterday [2 Aug 2018], according to the statement. The statement said that the patient had never been vaccinated against measles, but he has meanwhile recovered with no major complications. The statement added that his family members have not had any similar symptoms to date.

According to the statement, the bureau suggests that parents should avoid taking babies who have not been vaccinated against measles, especially those between the ages of 6 and 12 months, out of Macau because they will not have enough antibodies to protect them against measles.

